# BallouBot — Cline Rules

## Project Overview
BallouBot is a modular Discord bot built with **.NET 10**, **Discord.Net 3.19.1**, **EF Core 10** with **SQLite**, and **Serilog** for logging. It runs as a .NET Worker Service (`IHostedService`).

## Architecture

### Module System
- Modules live in `src/modules/BallouBot.Modules.*/` and implement `IModule` from `BallouBot.Core`
- Each module class is decorated with `[BotModule("id")]` for auto-discovery
- Modules register DI services in `ConfigureServices()` and hook Discord events in `InitializeAsync()`
- `IModuleContext` provides access to the `DiscordSocketClient`, `IServiceProvider`, and logging
- Modules are discovered from compiled-in assemblies (`BallouBot.Modules.*.dll`) and a drop-in `modules/` directory

### Key Projects
- `src/BallouBot.Core/` — Interfaces (`IModule`, `IModuleContext`, `IErrorNotificationService`), attributes, entities
- `src/BallouBot.Data/` — EF Core `BotDbContext`, migrations (SQLite)
- `src/BallouBot.Host/` — Entry point (`Program.cs`), `BotHostedService`, `ModuleLoader`, `ModuleContext`
- `src/modules/` — All module implementations

### Database
- Entities go in `src/BallouBot.Core/Entities/`
- `DbSet` properties and `OnModelCreating` config go in `src/BallouBot.Data/BotDbContext.cs`
- Migrations: `dotnet ef migrations add <Name> --project src/BallouBot.Data/BallouBot.Data.csproj --startup-project src/BallouBot.Host/BallouBot.Host.csproj`

### Testing
- Test framework: **TUnit** (v1.22.6) — uses `[Test]` attribute and `await Assert.That(...)` syntax
- DB tests use `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.InMemory`
- Test projects live in `tests/BallouBot.Modules.*.Tests/`
- Test csproj needs `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` for TUnit
- Run tests: `dotnet test --project tests/<ProjectName>/<ProjectName>.csproj`

## Current Modules
| Module | ID | Command | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| Welcome | `welcome` | — | Auto-welcomes new members |
| Random Richard | `randomrichard` | `/richard` | Random Richard interactions |
| Gif | `gif` | `/gif` | GIF search via Tenor |
| Fact Check | `factcheck` | `/factcheck` | AI-powered fact-checking of watched users |
| Help | `help` | `/balloubot help` | Lists all modules and commands |
| Error Notify | `errornotify` | `/balloubot errornotify @user` | DMs admins on bot errors |

## Conventions
- Always use **scoped DbContext** from event handlers (`using var scope = context.Services.CreateScope()`)
- Slash commands use **ephemeral responses** for configuration/admin commands
- Admin-only commands check `SocketGuildUser.GuildPermissions.Administrator`
- Error handling: wrap event handler logic in try/catch, log with structured parameters
- The `/balloubot` command is shared — multiple modules add subcommands to it (help, errornotify)
- Modules that share `/balloubot` must re-register the full command with all known subcommands

## Workflow
- Always run `dotnet build` to verify before committing
- Always run tests for affected modules before committing
- Commit with descriptive messages (summary + bullet points)
- Always push to remote after committing
- Solution file: `BallouBot.slnx` — add new projects with `dotnet sln add`

